Package cz.cuni.mff.d3s.trupple.language.runtime.exceptions

This package contains exceptions that may be thrown throughout the interpretation of a Pascal source file.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    BreakExceptionTP
    This exception is thrown when a Pascal's break statement is executed.
    CantReadInputException
    Exception thrown when we are unable to read from the input.
    EndOfFileException
    Exception is thrown when the user tries to read from a file but he has already reached its end.
    FileNotAssignedPathException
    Exception thrown when user tries to do I/O operation on a file variable but it has not assigned a path to a file.
    FileNotFoundException
    Exception thrown when a file with specified path can not be found.
    GotoException
    Exception is thrown when Pascal's goto statement is executed.
    HaltExceptionTP
    Exception thrown when Pascal's halt function is executed (HaltBuiltinNode).
    IndexOutOfBoundsException
    Exception thrown when user is accessing an array at non-existing index,
    LogarithmInvalidArgumentException
    Exception thrown when a user provides invalid argument for the logarithm function (LnBuiltinNode).
    NotOpenedToReadException
    Exception thrown when a user tries to read from a file that is not opened for reading.
    NotOpenedToWriteException
    Exception thrown when a user tries to write to a file that is not opened for writing.
    PascalRuntimeException
    A generic runtime exception with arbitrary message.
    SqrtInvalidArgumentException
    Exception thrown when a user provides invalid argument for the square root function (SqrtBuiltinNode).
    UnexpectedRuntimeException
    Generic runtime exception that is thrown when something unexpected has happened.

Package cz.cuni.mff.d3s.trupple.language.runtime.exceptions Description

This package contains exceptions that may be thrown throughout the interpretation of a Pascal source file.
